DUTSE – The Emir of Dutse, Jigawa State, HRH Alh. Nuhu Muhammadu Sanusi, has said no nation will achieve greatness without well developed institution’s of learning. Sanusi stated this at a civic reception organised by Dutse Emirate to honoured its illustrious son and daughter who excelled in different fields of academics held at the emir’s palace in Garu-Dutse, in Jigawa State. He reaffirm the commitment of Dutse Emirate to collaborate with individuals or organisation wishing to contribute towards the development of the emirate. In his message’s, Governor Badaru Abubakar, represented by the Secretary to the State Government (SSG), Alh. Adamu Fanini, commended the Emir and Dutse Emirate for organising such a unique reception. He reiterated the state government’s resolve to accord priority to key economic sectors such as education, health, agriculture, and commerce to achieve the desired objectives. During the reception, 11 professors, 55 PhD holders and 34 students who recently bagged first class degrees from various universities were honoured.